{
  "texts": [
    "BackgroundThe rapidly increasing advancements in artificial intelligence (AI), deep learning, and machine learning (ML) have revolutionized a wide range of sectors, including business [1], healthcare [2], entertainment [3], and education [4].",
    "Generative AI, a component of ML which can generate content in a number of formats such as text, audio, images, video and computer code is finding applications in various fields such as content creation, data analysis, software development, virtual assistance, simulation, and personalized education [4][5][6][7].",
    "Large language models (LLMs), a subset of generative AI are ML algorithms that employ vast amounts of text for analysis and generate responses [8].",
    "LLMs such as Chat Generative Pre-Trained Transformer (ChatGPT), a program developed by Open AI, and Gemini, formerly called Bard, built by Google AI, have gained popularity due to their ability to generate human-like replies and easy accessibility [9,10].",
    "With increasing incorporation of AI into numerous aspects of healthcare delivery, its integration with medical education is impending."
  ]
}